I have a working patch to let you use enums in place of EnumeratedAttribute,
which is more convenient and intuitive if you are using JDK 5 anyway. Example:

<project default="x">
    <target name="x">
        <echo file="T.java">
            public class T extends org.apache.tools.ant.Task {
                public enum E {
                    first,
                    second,
                    third
                }
                private E thing;
                public void setThing(E e) {
                    thing = e;
                }
                public void execute() {
                    log("thing=" + thing);
                }
            }
        </echo>
        <javac srcdir="." destdir="." includes="T.java"/>
        <taskdef name="twaddle" classname="T" classpath="."/>
        <twaddle thing="third"/>
        <antstructure output="ant.dtd"/>
        <loadfile srcfile="ant.dtd" property="ant.dtd"/>
        <echo>${ant.dtd}</echo>
    </target>
</project>

I would commit it right now but there does not seem to be a branch for 1.7 yet
and I am reluctant to add features to a release in the RC phase.
